---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<base href="https://soughspeck.github.io/my-portfolio/">

<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Anna Hyatt</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
<Layout>

  <main>
    <div class="container-intro">
        <div class="hero">
        Hey, I'm Anna<br>I'm a product designer with a 7 years of experience in data-centered and dev products. I have been working both in <a class="case-study-link"
          >aÂ fast-paced tech start-up</a>
        and <a class="case-study-link">a large national institution.</a>
        </div>
      
        <section class="section-divider"></section>

        <!-- DagsHub Section -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-content">
          <h2>DagsHub</h2>
          <p class="subtitle">2022-now | Lead Product Designer | MLOps, B2B/B2C</p>
          
          <p>
              <a href="https://www.dagshub.com">DagsHub</a> is an MLOps platform that helps companies to manage full AI training cycle all-in-one place.
          </p>
          
          <p>
              I led the company's product design, through its evolution from a community platform to an enterprise solution. Over 2,5 years, I designed and shipped UX improvements for the whole platform, as well as led a major pivotal feature from ideation to production, which helped us double the amount of customers. Also:
          </p>
          
          <ul>
              <li>I established processes for effective collaboration with devs (built and shipped company's first Design System, led Figma Workshop for developers)</li>
              <li>Drove end-to-end redesigns of essential user flows focusing on activation, simplification and retention (conducted usability testing, identified friction points via user recordings observation)</li>
              <li>Promoted user-centered decision-making (conducted user surveys, analyzed sales talks to identify customer expectation gaps)</li>
              <li>Nurtured UX maturity in the company (weekly User Recordings Replays, UX Updates Newsletter)</li>
          </ul>
      </div>
      

      <div class="section-image dagshub-image">
          <video src="assets/dagshub-data-engine-video.mp4" width="100%" autoplay="" loop="" playsinline="">Your browser does not support the video tag.</video>


          
      </div>
  </section>
      <!-- National Library of Israel Section -->
    <section class="section reverse">
      <div class="section-content">
          <h2>The National Library of Israel | Digital</h2>
          <p class="subtitle">2018-2022 | UI/UX Designer in a Product Team | Cultural Heritage, Digital Archive, B2C</p>
          
          <p>
              At the National Library of Israel, our product team kept the site updated, usable, and engaging. I worked on site architecture, search engine improvements, and new content pages, prioritizing SEO and usability. These efforts brought 3M additional users to the platform.
          </p>
          
          <p>Over 5 years in the Library, I was:</p>
          
          <ul>
              <li>Part of a design and product team that led end-to-end design for core NLI products, including benchmarking, wireframing, and QA.</li>
              <li>Revamped site architecture with an SEO-first approach.</li>
              <li>Designed dozens of page templates and features, enhancing data accessibility and user experience.</li>
              <li>Established NLI's first Design System as part of the design team.</li>
              <li>The team achieved remarkable growth in monthly sessions, rising from 70,000 in 2018 to 1,900,000 in 2020, with a projected 4,000,000 by 2023.</li>
          </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="section-image">
        <div class="section-image" style="background: url('assets/nli-search-redesign.jpeg') no-repeat center center; background-size: cover; width: 100%; height: 100%; min-height: 400px;">
      </div>
    </section>

    <style>
        
      .section {
          display: flex;
          flex-direction: column;
          margin-bottom: 60px;
          gap: 24px;
        
      }
      
      .section-divider {
        border-top: 0.5px #2600ff solid;
        padding-top: 60px;
      }

      .section-content {
          width: 100%;
      }
      
      .section-image {
          width: 100%;
          display: flex;
          align-items: center;
          justify-content: center;
          padding: 1rem;
          border-radius: 8px;
      }
      
      .section-image img {
          max-width: 100%;
      }
      
      a {
        color:#2600ff;
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      .dagshub-image {
          background-color: #2600ff;
          
      }
      
      .nli-image {
          background-color: #14b8a6;
      }
      
      h2 {
          font-size: 18px;
          font-weight: 700;
          color: #1f2937;
      }
      
      .subtitle {
        font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;  
        font-size: 14px;
          color: #64748B;
        
      }
      
      .company-name {
          color: #2563eb;
          font-weight: 500;
      }
      
      p {
        font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 16px;
      }
      
      ul {
          
          font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
          font-size: 16px;
          
          
      }
      
      li {
          margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
          position: relative;
          
      }
      
      @media (min-width: 800px) {
          .section {
              flex-direction: row;
          }
          
          .section-content {
              width: 50%;
          }
          
          .section-image {
              width: 50%;
          }
          
          .section.reverse {
              flex-direction: row-reverse;
          }
      }
  </style>

  </main>
  
</Layout>

</body>
</html>
